Lists Details

Get list by Title
-http://server/site/_api/lists/getbytitle(‘listname’)

URL	        	 

Details|Method
Get data from SharePoint list|GET
/_api/Web/Lists/getbytitle(‘yourListName’)	

Get List Item by Column Value|GET
/_api/web/Lists/getByTitle(‘Student’)/items?$filter=’Internal Name of the column’ eq “Some value	

Getting data and adding data in a list/GET/POST
/_api/Web/Lists/getbytitle(‘listname’)/Items
/_api/web/lists/getbytitle(‘listname’)

Get, update and delete a single item	GET, PUT, PATCH, MERGE, DELETE
/GetItemById(itemId)

Retrieve lookup value	   GET/POST
/_api/web/lists/getbytitle(‘listname’)/Items/?$select=Title,FieldName/Id&$expand= FieldName /Id	

Update records	POST/MERGE
/_api/web/lists/GetByTitle(‘Your List Name’)/items(Your record ID)	
/_api/web/lists/GetByTitle(‘Your List Name’)/items(Your record ID)	Delete Records	POST/DELETE
$filter=AuthorId eq <UserId>  	Get list item created by logged in user	          GET
$filter=StartDate ge datetime'” + today.toISOString()  	Filter date based on Start Date	          GET
/_api/lists/getbytitle (‘’listname’)/items?$orderby=Title	
Getting data order by column	       GET
/_api/web/lists/getbytitle(‘StoryDate’)/Items?$filter=Created leq ’11/24/2015′	Filter date using created column	          GET
